1
00:00:44,834 --> 00:00:48,971
Just for a while, that's all I need.

2
00:00:50,307 --> 00:00:52,609
Let me just hold it for a minute.

3
00:00:58,486 --> 00:01:01,556
As always, your hands comfort me.

4
00:01:01,556 --> 00:01:03,625
What happened?

5
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:05,360
Sunbae...

6
00:01:06,154 --> 00:01:08,430
It's strange.

7
00:01:08,430 --> 00:01:13,872
Professor Do Kang Jae came in for my lesson
instead of Professor Ahn.

8
00:01:13,872 --> 00:01:16,474
I'm Professor Ahn's student.

9
00:01:17,245 --> 00:01:20,742
Professor Do doesn't have a good personality

10
00:01:20,742 --> 00:01:22,753
but he's the best in the piano major.

11
00:01:22,753 --> 00:01:25,079
Don't you know
it's a good opportunity for you?

12
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:27,581
I know Professor Ahn is nice...

13
00:01:28,337 --> 00:01:30,628
but you need a strict teacher.

14
00:01:30,628 --> 00:01:34,922
- I don't need a strict teacher.
- You do.

15
00:01:34,922 --> 00:01:36,791
That's how you can improve.

16
00:01:40,095 --> 00:01:42,197
He asked me about your talent...

17
00:01:42,197 --> 00:01:46,034
So I told him that you'd change
if you met a good leader.

18
00:01:46,034 --> 00:01:51,506
But a lesson already...
Professor Do sure is fast.

19
00:02:04,619 --> 00:02:06,688
Yes, Professor.

20
00:02:06,688 --> 00:02:08,856
Seol Nae Il is with me.

21
00:02:09,691 --> 00:02:11,459
I'll bring her.

22
00:02:14,395 --> 00:02:16,626
Let's go. He's still waiting for you.

23
00:02:16,626 --> 00:02:18,399
Let's go get your lesson...

24
00:02:22,691 --> 00:02:24,943
Seol Nae Il.

25
00:02:24,943 --> 00:02:26,664
I don't want to.

26
00:02:28,113 --> 00:02:33,882
I don't need any good opportunities.

27
00:02:33,882 --> 00:02:40,254
Crying, getting hit, getting hurt,
and being in pain everyday...

28
00:02:43,258 --> 00:02:48,262
"That's how you become a successful pianist.
You must!"

29
00:02:49,130 --> 00:02:51,966
I really don't need any of that.

30
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:54,903
So why do you keep forcing me?

31
00:02:54,903 --> 00:02:59,273
I said I don't want harsh lessons,
so why do you keep on insisting?

32
00:03:02,544 --> 00:03:06,547
You're just the same.

33
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:10,985
You're just the same as those people.

34
00:03:24,979 --> 00:03:27,067
What are you afraid of?

35
00:03:27,067 --> 00:03:30,342
His yelling? Getting hit by his fan?

36
00:03:30,342 --> 00:03:32,545
Is that why you're running away?

37
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:34,846
Don't you think you're wasting your talents?

38
00:03:34,846 --> 00:03:40,752
You talk just like those people.

39
00:03:42,896 --> 00:03:46,837
When everyone says the same thing,
that means you're wrong.

40
00:03:46,837 --> 00:03:49,557
I just can't help it...

41
00:03:51,252 --> 00:03:53,587
You don't know what it's like.

42
00:03:54,415 --> 00:03:57,518
It's not that I'm not doing it.
I just can't do it.

43
00:03:58,612 --> 00:04:01,331
I can't help it...

44
00:04:01,331 --> 00:04:03,600
That's why I'm more scared.

45
00:04:04,572 --> 00:04:07,642
People like you wouldn't know.

46
00:04:12,947 --> 00:04:14,795
Wait, Seol Nae Il.

47
00:04:14,795 --> 00:04:16,184
Seol Nae Il!

48
00:04:16,184 --> 00:04:19,004
Let go of me! I'm not talking to you!

49
00:04:19,004 --> 00:04:21,256
Calm down and let's talk.

50
00:04:21,256 --> 00:04:22,545
I know about that, too.

51
00:04:22,545 --> 00:04:25,359
- I'm not talking to you.
- Seol Nae Il...

52
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:29,700
Seol Nae Il...

53
00:04:50,918 --> 00:04:52,920
You sure are very consistent.

54
00:04:54,355 --> 00:04:58,826
Always insisting things in your way...
Always being rude...

55
00:05:00,528 --> 00:05:02,964
I told you not to mistreat women.

56
00:05:02,964 --> 00:05:04,899
You are consistently nosy, too.

57
00:05:06,134 --> 00:05:07,068
Mind your own business.

58
00:05:07,068 --> 00:05:09,337
You should mind your own business.

59
00:05:11,339 --> 00:05:14,442
Seol Nae Il, let's talk.

60
00:06:30,251 --> 00:06:32,853
Autumn in Korea is really beautiful.

61
00:06:34,041 --> 00:06:36,944
Isn't it amazing?

62
00:06:36,944 --> 00:06:40,381
A variety of colors come out
of one single tree.

63
00:06:49,817 --> 00:06:52,837
The sound of stepping on the fallen leaves
is delicious.

64
00:06:52,837 --> 00:06:54,942
It sounds just like eating a snack.

65
00:06:56,511 --> 00:06:58,546
Aren't you hungry?

66
00:07:00,648 --> 00:07:04,795
Yoo Jin Sunbae must be really angry.

67
00:07:04,795 --> 00:07:07,045
I got mad at him...

68
00:07:07,045 --> 00:07:10,336
Cha Yoo Jin yells at you a lot, too.

69
00:07:10,336 --> 00:07:13,828
Then you can get mad and yell at him, too.

70
00:07:16,183 --> 00:07:19,420
But still, I shouldn't have done that.

71
00:07:22,276 --> 00:07:27,247
Right, because Nae Il likes him.

72
00:07:29,219 --> 00:07:34,962
He wouldn't see me anymore, would he?

73
00:07:34,962 --> 00:07:37,628
He threw out all my stuff...

74
00:07:37,628 --> 00:07:40,968
He changed the door code...

75
00:07:40,968 --> 00:07:46,006
I got mad and yelled at him
saying I wouldn't get lessons from Professor Do.

76
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:54,561
He must really hate me now, right?

77
00:07:56,109 --> 00:07:57,844
Right?

78
00:08:01,381 --> 00:08:06,353
It's really over now between Sunbae and me.

79
00:08:27,883 --> 00:08:30,185
So it's over now...

80
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,655
between Cha Yoo Jin and you.

81
00:08:38,045 --> 00:08:44,285
No, I don't need any good opportunities.

82
00:08:44,285 --> 00:08:51,258
Crying, getting hit, getting hurt
and being in pain everyday...

83
00:08:51,959 --> 00:08:56,497
"That's how you can become a successful pianist.
You must!''

84
00:08:58,907 --> 00:09:01,509
You said you'd bring Seol Nae Il.

85
00:09:02,637 --> 00:09:04,962
- She left.
- What?

86
00:09:04,962 --> 00:09:08,545
Am I just no such big deal to all of you?

87
00:09:08,545 --> 00:09:11,378
Is it her hobby and specialty
to run away in the middle of playing the piano?

88
00:09:11,378 --> 00:09:13,420
Once at Yoon Yi Song Music Festival,
and this time again?

89
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,712
The stick before the carrot...

90
00:09:15,712 --> 00:09:20,878
I forgot that Professor Yoon Yi Song
and your teaching styles are similar.

91
00:09:20,878 --> 00:09:22,795
What are you saying?

92
00:09:22,795 --> 00:09:24,959
Please, Professor.

93
00:09:30,105 --> 00:09:31,086
What's wrong with you?

94
00:09:31,086 --> 00:09:35,670
I only thought about Seol Nae Il's talent.

95
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:37,253
She's still a kid.

96
00:09:37,253 --> 00:09:38,211
She just runs away

97
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:40,128
from things she doesn't like
and things she's scared of.

98
00:09:40,128 --> 00:09:42,243
I forgot about that.

99
00:09:43,865 --> 00:09:48,135
That kid still needs time.

100
00:10:05,399 --> 00:10:07,568
I don't want to practice piano.

101
00:10:16,497 --> 00:10:19,169
I'm going to become a kindergarten teacher.

102
00:10:19,169 --> 00:10:22,416
I wish I didn't have
that thing called 'talent.'

103
00:10:23,957 --> 00:10:26,502
Nae Il...

104
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:30,751
then you couldn't have came to college
and met Yoo Jin Sunbae.

105
00:10:30,751 --> 00:10:34,918
I don't like Yoo Jin Sunbae either.
He told you to go to Professor Do.

106
00:10:34,918 --> 00:10:37,698
But he did that for me.

107
00:10:38,854 --> 00:10:43,759
Not doing anything you don't want,
and hiding when you get scared...

108
00:10:45,318 --> 00:10:47,584
let's not do that anymore.

109
00:10:47,584 --> 00:10:52,334
You said you liked living like me.
But you changed.

110
00:10:52,334 --> 00:10:58,633
Yoo Jin will look at me as a kid
just like you.

111
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:00,542
I don't want that.

112
00:11:00,542 --> 00:11:03,209
To Yoo Jin, you are me.

113
00:11:03,209 --> 00:11:06,584
Even when he did something wrong,
he never apologized to you.

114
00:11:06,584 --> 00:11:08,477
He just got angry at you again today.

115
00:11:08,477 --> 00:11:11,312
I'm sure he's not like that to other people.

116
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:19,839
Am I really you to Sunbae?

117
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:45,376
[Yoo Il Lak - Idiot 2]

118
00:11:46,878 --> 00:11:49,878
Well, Cha Yoo Jin.

119
00:11:49,878 --> 00:11:52,413
Since when did you need a friend?

120
00:12:13,742 --> 00:12:16,542
Three, two, one!

121
00:12:16,542 --> 00:12:18,480
Nae Il is coming in!

122
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:24,754
Right, I changed my code.

123
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:27,489
She can't come in.

124
00:12:31,593 --> 00:12:33,495
Let's talk.

125
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:03,417
- Give me my stuff back.
- What stuff?

126
00:13:03,417 --> 00:13:06,361
There is more than what was in the box.

127
00:13:06,829 --> 00:13:09,431
You were looking for them
a few days ago.

128
00:13:10,431 --> 00:13:12,867
I know you have a lot of them in there.

129
00:13:14,023 --> 00:13:18,294
I don't have them.

130
00:13:19,374 --> 00:13:21,075
Why not?

131
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:23,911
Did you throw them all out?

132
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:30,385
You really threw them all out.

133
00:13:31,250 --> 00:13:33,759
You should've saved them until I came.

134
00:13:33,759 --> 00:13:37,684
- No, it's not that...
- Just like Yoon Hoo said...

135
00:13:38,289 --> 00:13:41,392
You're really mean.

136
00:13:44,163 --> 00:13:47,006
Why do you bring him up here?

137
00:13:47,006 --> 00:13:49,134
You don't know
what you've done wrong, do you?

138
00:13:49,134 --> 00:13:51,051
I admit that I was impatient.

139
00:13:51,051 --> 00:13:53,759
We can't live like this anyway...

140
00:13:53,759 --> 00:13:58,271
If you think you've done something wrong,
why can't you just apologize?

141
00:14:00,313 --> 00:14:02,849
Don't try to make me understand...

142
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:06,446
Can't you just say "I'm sorry"?

143
00:14:07,902 --> 00:14:10,175
I apologize to you everyday.

144
00:14:10,175 --> 00:14:12,819
I don't even know what's going on,
but I still say so...

145
00:14:13,587 --> 00:14:17,290
So why don't you do that to me? Why?

146
00:14:18,651 --> 00:14:21,386
Am I not even worth apologizing?

147
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:25,331
Seol Nae Il...

148
00:14:40,726 --> 00:14:43,175
They should be mentioning
about the orchestra rule by now

149
00:14:43,175 --> 00:14:45,618
but I feel more anxious
that there's not even a word.

150
00:14:46,519 --> 00:14:48,554
Min Hee, seven on white.

151
00:14:51,191 --> 00:14:53,051
What do we do?

152
00:14:53,051 --> 00:14:54,926
As we had a good performance,

153
00:14:54,926 --> 00:14:57,564
I was hoping to get a call from somewhere...

154
00:14:58,493 --> 00:15:01,134
I don't even have money
to go study abroad.

155
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:03,937
I need two build my career at an orchestra.

156
00:15:05,224 --> 00:15:07,827
Su Min, you have seven.

157
00:15:09,796 --> 00:15:12,384
Do I have to study for TOEIC now?

158
00:15:12,384 --> 00:15:14,759
You can go back to A.

159
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:16,116
Why worry about getting a job?

160
00:15:16,116 --> 00:15:17,759
He's not a migratory bird.

161
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:19,786
How can he go back
to the place he abandoned?

162
00:15:21,848 --> 00:15:23,997
Why aren't you saying anything?

163
00:15:23,997 --> 00:15:25,498
I play timpani.

164
00:15:26,105 --> 00:15:28,508
At least you can practice on your own...

165
00:15:29,396 --> 00:15:31,297
What am I supposed to do?

166
00:15:32,051 --> 00:15:33,384
We lasted for long.

167
00:15:33,384 --> 00:15:35,592
You can just get married.

168
00:15:35,592 --> 00:15:37,637
Are you making it obvious
you came to music school

169
00:15:37,637 --> 00:15:39,384
to raise your price on the market?

170
00:15:39,384 --> 00:15:40,676
What?

171
00:15:40,676 --> 00:15:42,371
You're only thinking
about making the right connections.

172
00:15:42,371 --> 00:15:43,443
What?

173
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,926
Stop.

174
00:15:44,926 --> 00:15:47,259
What's the point of arguing with each other?

175
00:15:47,259 --> 00:15:49,816
He's right. Sit down.

176
00:15:54,587 --> 00:15:56,523
I'll wait for you in the practice room.

177
00:15:56,523 --> 00:15:58,558
Jung Shi Won.

178
00:16:07,667 --> 00:16:10,670
I'm busy. I can't go. Sorry.

179
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:13,573
You're the one who decided the time.

180
00:16:13,573 --> 00:16:16,109
Did something happen to him?

181
00:16:16,109 --> 00:16:18,945
You know, the 'rock spirit' guy.

182
00:16:18,945 --> 00:16:20,413
You're hanging out with him often these days.

183
00:16:20,413 --> 00:16:24,117
We're performing together.
We have to practice.

184
00:16:24,117 --> 00:16:26,619
Are you having a fling with him?

185
00:16:26,619 --> 00:16:29,589
I wonder if he knows the real you.
Your behavior when you get drunk...

186
00:16:29,589 --> 00:16:31,658
Shut up.

187
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:33,559
Even violence.

188
00:16:46,406 --> 00:16:49,809
I'm sorry, Shi Won.
We're Romeo and Juliet now.

189
00:16:56,383 --> 00:16:59,252
That punk, I haven't even gotten
to the shoulders...

190
00:17:13,366 --> 00:17:15,702
My son, are you meditating?

191
00:17:15,702 --> 00:17:17,937
Why don't you do that in your room?

192
00:17:17,937 --> 00:17:20,340
- Father...
- What, What?

193
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:23,200
You don't want to walk up the steps?
Do you want me to carry you?

194
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:30,216
The sky is very dark.
Everything's dark and gloomy.

195
00:17:31,251 --> 00:17:33,786
Because it's night time.

196
00:17:34,901 --> 00:17:39,539
Everyone's eating so well.
What do they find so delicious?

197
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:42,662
It's because they are my dishes!

198
00:17:42,662 --> 00:17:46,699
Yes, right.
My father's cooking is really good.

199
00:17:48,922 --> 00:17:52,558
I'm going to my room, Father.
I'll be a good son later.

200
00:17:59,132 --> 00:18:01,981
Just keep breathing,
that's being a good son to me.

201
00:18:01,981 --> 00:18:03,750
Careful, careful...

202
00:18:06,973 --> 00:18:08,175
That's exactly what I did

203
00:18:08,175 --> 00:18:12,759
when I got stood up
on the first date with his mother.

204
00:18:18,631 --> 00:18:23,949
I thought I should get permission
from you first.

205
00:18:23,949 --> 00:18:28,759
Once S Orchestra is dissolved
and we proceed with this,

206
00:18:28,759 --> 00:18:32,092
everyone will be suspicious of you.

207
00:18:32,092 --> 00:18:33,313
I know that.

208
00:18:33,313 --> 00:18:36,583
It'll be tougher for you than you think.

209
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:39,986
It can take a long time
before other students understand you.

210
00:18:42,008 --> 00:18:47,713
I asked myself many times,
the question you asked me.

211
00:18:49,395 --> 00:18:51,831
But I kept getting the same answer.

212
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:55,735
Let's choose the less-tough route.

213
00:18:59,746 --> 00:19:03,950
Being misunderstood will be less tough.

214
00:19:05,618 --> 00:19:10,383
They look as if they're just hanging out
without any sense.

215
00:19:10,383 --> 00:19:12,318
But they're living intense lives.

216
00:19:13,219 --> 00:19:15,555
The things I enjoyed as a given...

217
00:19:15,555 --> 00:19:19,526
They had to fight for them
and make an effort to earn them.

218
00:19:19,526 --> 00:19:22,629
A lot of us improved
because of your advice.

219
00:19:22,629 --> 00:19:25,498
Help us once more!

220
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:30,736
I'm sorry I'm late. I'm Contrabass.

221
00:19:32,369 --> 00:19:37,010
I considered the dream of studying abroad
as given for music students.

222
00:19:37,010 --> 00:19:38,978
But they gave up on it
from the beginning.

223
00:19:39,992 --> 00:19:46,165
They are giving up so much
to be in the orchestra.

224
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,736
You know the reason, right?

225
00:19:51,991 --> 00:19:57,230
And that's why you planned this, right?

226
00:19:58,668 --> 00:20:03,467
Once they graduate,
most of them will lose their music spirit.

227
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:07,940
But S Orchestra gave them the hope
that they can be with music.

228
00:20:08,948 --> 00:20:11,150
I want to grow that hope for them.

229
00:20:12,912 --> 00:20:15,718
That's what you dreamed of.

230
00:20:15,718 --> 00:20:18,939
Even without connections
and tough lessons...

231
00:20:18,939 --> 00:20:21,759
an orchestra that grows with their sweat.

232
00:20:21,759 --> 00:20:25,391
So let's bet our adventure on it.

233
00:20:26,259 --> 00:20:29,895
They've changed
through the performances so far.

234
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,467
Let's bet our adventure on them.

235
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:36,903
We have no other path anyway.

236
00:20:49,649 --> 00:20:53,986
S Orchestra is dissolved.
Please make an announcement.

237
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:32,709
Dissolution?

238
00:21:32,709 --> 00:21:35,000
[S Orchestra Dissolution]

239
00:22:03,209 --> 00:22:08,509
Which orchestra would you choose
if you were in my place?

240
00:22:08,509 --> 00:22:09,395
Pardon?

241
00:22:09,395 --> 00:22:14,301
Is it A that has tradition, effort and talent?

242
00:22:14,301 --> 00:22:19,739
Or is it S that has free spirit?

243
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:23,542
You should think about it.

244
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:28,814
Now I'm going to find an answer
to that question.

245
00:22:29,614 --> 00:22:33,718
Not by myself, but together.

246
00:22:36,122 --> 00:22:39,134
Have we really been dissolved?

247
00:22:39,134 --> 00:22:41,010
So this is the end?

248
00:22:41,010 --> 00:22:44,697
Think about how we hung in.
This is too harsh!

249
00:22:45,502 --> 00:22:48,384
It's the school rule. Can't blame anyone.

250
00:22:48,384 --> 00:22:50,843
What will I tell my father?

251
00:22:50,843 --> 00:22:53,839
He liked Mambo, so he said he'd come again.

252
00:23:10,042 --> 00:23:11,750
[A Orchestra Dissolution]

253
00:23:15,378 --> 00:23:20,250
[A Orchestra Dissolution]
[S Orchestra Dissolutiont]

254
00:23:20,654 --> 00:23:21,955
Madam Dean!

255
00:23:25,107 --> 00:23:26,975
Madam Dean!

256
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:32,243
What the heck are you doing?
What's on your mind?

257
00:23:32,243 --> 00:23:37,333
The rule says one orchestra in the school.

258
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:40,166
There is no decision on which orchestra.

259
00:23:40,166 --> 00:23:41,791
Isn't that right?

260
00:23:41,791 --> 00:23:43,485
Dean...

261
00:23:45,802 --> 00:23:48,666
Does it make sense?
I won't believe it until I see it.

262
00:23:48,666 --> 00:23:50,000
I heard it's true.

263
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,629
How can the dean do this?

264
00:23:51,629 --> 00:23:53,666
- There must be some mistake.
- It is a mistake!

265
00:23:53,666 --> 00:23:55,916
Why would ours be dissolved with S?

266
00:23:55,916 --> 00:23:57,791
A is dissolved too? Why?

267
00:23:57,791 --> 00:24:00,238
It's not like,
buy one get one free, or anything.

268
00:24:00,238 --> 00:24:02,207
Maybe the school regulation changed, Lak.

269
00:24:02,207 --> 00:24:06,042
Get rid of all school orchestras...

270
00:24:06,042 --> 00:24:08,416
That's nonsense!

271
00:24:08,416 --> 00:24:13,916
Most of them in A Orchestra are daughters,
nieces and relatives of the executives.

272
00:24:13,916 --> 00:24:17,166
- What?
- Then it doesn't matter if it's dissolved.

273
00:24:17,166 --> 00:24:20,558
They'll go study abroad
after graduating from school here anyway.

274
00:24:23,258 --> 00:24:25,593
Where do I go now?

275
00:24:27,818 --> 00:24:30,521
My Shi Won must be shocked.

276
00:24:44,277 --> 00:24:47,207
I'll make an announcement
about the dissolution of the orchestras

277
00:24:47,207 --> 00:24:49,720
based on the revised regulation.

278
00:24:50,808 --> 00:24:54,645
S Orchestra and A Orchestra
are both dissolved.

279
00:24:55,237 --> 00:24:57,708
It's not a simple dissolution.

280
00:24:57,708 --> 00:25:00,166
It's the first step of a new beginning.

281
00:25:00,166 --> 00:25:05,436
We'll establish a new orchestra
after an audition process.

282
00:25:07,372 --> 00:25:11,416
A new orchestra
that will represent our Han Eum

283
00:25:11,416 --> 00:25:13,978
will be created.

284
00:25:15,185 --> 00:25:19,756
And the conductor of the new orchestra is...

285
00:25:24,594 --> 00:25:29,733
Mr. Cha Yoo Jin,
former conductor of S Orchestra.

286
00:25:32,577 --> 00:25:34,512
Almighty Cha?

287
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:37,768
Sunbae?

288
00:25:49,259 --> 00:25:52,517
After dissolving the orchestra
that represents our school...

289
00:25:52,517 --> 00:25:55,273
you think you'll be safe with your title?

290
00:25:55,273 --> 00:26:00,166
S Orchestra is also representative
after a successful performance this time.

291
00:26:00,166 --> 00:26:06,297
You dissolved the orchestra
that represents Han Eum just to save S?

292
00:26:06,297 --> 00:26:09,875
A new orchestra...
What on earth are you thinking?

293
00:26:09,875 --> 00:26:12,403
I'll bet my dean title on it.

294
00:26:18,009 --> 00:26:21,512
If it fails, I'll leave my job.

295
00:26:22,513 --> 00:26:24,515
Would you believe me now?

296
00:26:30,675 --> 00:26:32,875
It looks like a rash move

297
00:26:32,875 --> 00:26:35,374
but it's impossible to
establish a new orchestra

298
00:26:35,374 --> 00:26:37,323
without dissolving them.

299
00:26:38,169 --> 00:26:40,958
Not as a resume builder
and a step before studying abroad

300
00:26:40,958 --> 00:26:45,036
but I plan to build a real orchestra
managed with passion.

301
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:49,624
Just like
Vienna Philharmonic and Berlin Philharmonic...

302
00:26:49,624 --> 00:26:54,312
a brand orchestra
that represents a city and a country.

303
00:26:55,319 --> 00:26:57,388
With that dreamlike words...

304
00:26:59,143 --> 00:27:02,186
the dean created S Orchestra.

305
00:27:02,186 --> 00:27:04,916
That dreamlike orchestra...

306
00:27:04,916 --> 00:27:07,249
I'm going to create that now.

307
00:27:07,249 --> 00:27:10,328
The orchestra that has the individuality of S

308
00:27:10,328 --> 00:27:13,791
and the technique and experience of A.

309
00:27:13,791 --> 00:27:14,875
Are you saying

310
00:27:14,875 --> 00:27:18,636
that the orchestra that represents Han Eum
is worse than S?

311
00:27:18,636 --> 00:27:21,105
Individual skills are outstanding.

312
00:27:21,105 --> 00:27:23,741
But the problem with A is...

313
00:27:25,630 --> 00:27:27,965
the standardized melody.

314
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:32,721
The sound was created based on a formula,
just like a correct answer.

315
00:27:32,721 --> 00:27:37,622
Exact guidance and calculated performance
that tell you who their teacher is.

316
00:27:37,622 --> 00:27:42,026
Not their own performance,
but the performance that judges want.

317
00:27:42,026 --> 00:27:44,762
It can't draw out emotions.

318
00:27:47,295 --> 00:27:53,301
On the other hand, the individual skills of S
are definitely below those of A.

319
00:27:55,073 --> 00:27:57,441
Free spirit that breaks away from the norm.

320
00:27:58,242 --> 00:28:02,780
That's probably not the right answer
that the music industry wants.

321
00:28:03,935 --> 00:28:08,416
Professor von Stresemann once threw me
a question

322
00:28:08,416 --> 00:28:10,684
about the two orchestras.

323
00:28:10,684 --> 00:28:15,083
That was only a part of the plan
to create a new orchestra.

324
00:28:15,083 --> 00:28:17,906
Everyone knows
about the strengths and weaknesses of both!

325
00:28:19,643 --> 00:28:21,666
The issue is fairness.

326
00:28:21,666 --> 00:28:25,536
Therefore I suggest a blind audition.

327
00:28:31,343 --> 00:28:33,791
Blind audition?

328
00:28:33,791 --> 00:28:36,414
Then people won't complain afterwards.

329
00:28:36,414 --> 00:28:39,383
It will depend completely on competency.

330
00:28:42,035 --> 00:28:46,023
Then who'd judge that audition?

331
00:28:46,023 --> 00:28:49,293
Cha Yoo Jin, by any chance?

332
00:28:52,516 --> 00:28:58,555
Professor Ahn Geon Sung and Do Kang Jae
who led S and A Orchestras.

333
00:29:00,505 --> 00:29:03,000
We'll accept students
as the orchestra members

334
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,177
only after they pass through
both of the professors.

335
00:29:06,177 --> 00:29:08,879
It will resolve the fairness issue.

336
00:29:16,387 --> 00:29:17,788
Ma'am!

337
00:29:19,244 --> 00:29:21,166
Will you do what Cha Yoo Jin said?

338
00:29:21,166 --> 00:29:22,750
It's just the dean's trick.

339
00:29:22,750 --> 00:29:25,930
Trick or not,
she's setting up something beneficial to us.

340
00:29:27,064 --> 00:29:28,699
What are you afraid of?

341
00:29:28,699 --> 00:29:33,875
You know who is S or A
when you hear a student play.

342
00:29:33,875 --> 00:29:36,407
I do.

343
00:29:36,407 --> 00:29:40,289
People have been talking behind our backs,
but the controversy will disappear.

344
00:29:40,289 --> 00:29:43,833
Even after its foundation,
it will be deep in the mountain.

345
00:29:43,833 --> 00:29:48,019
Does she believe
it'll settle down without sponsorship?

346
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,454
How naive.

347
00:30:11,189 --> 00:30:15,860
First violin, bandmaster Jung Shi Won.

348
00:30:16,569 --> 00:30:20,106
Second violin, Yoo Il Lak.

349
00:30:21,191 --> 00:30:23,927
Viola, Lee Dan Ya.

350
00:30:24,815 --> 00:30:27,618
First oboe, Goo Seon Jae.

351
00:30:29,312 --> 00:30:31,514
Trumpet, Lee Jay Young.

352
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:34,958
Horn, Kim Yoo Jin.

353
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:37,935
Double bass, Choi Min Hee.

354
00:30:38,758 --> 00:30:41,560
Timpani, Ma Su Min.

355
00:30:43,307 --> 00:30:46,710
First cello, Lee Yoon Hoo.

356
00:30:48,977 --> 00:30:51,245
You, just go away.

357
00:31:09,205 --> 00:31:10,706
Hey, Yoo Il Lak!

358
00:31:11,442 --> 00:31:13,311
Hey, Yoo Il Lak!

359
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:18,442
It's been a long time
since I deleted your number.

360
00:31:18,442 --> 00:31:20,578
You're just 'no name' to me.

361
00:31:20,578 --> 00:31:22,346
You haven't heard yet?

362
00:31:22,346 --> 00:31:25,516
A new orchestra will be created
through blind auditions.

363
00:31:25,516 --> 00:31:26,958
We heard, Almighty Cha.

364
00:31:26,958 --> 00:31:29,353
We just met with Professor Ahn.

365
00:31:29,353 --> 00:31:34,124
- You're trying to dismiss us, right?
- What do you mean?

366
00:31:34,124 --> 00:31:36,961
How can we defeat A as soloists?

367
00:31:36,961 --> 00:31:40,261
If we fail one after another,
doesn't it mean to tell us, 'know your place'?

368
00:31:41,444 --> 00:31:44,249
- You have no confidence?
- Of course we don't.

369
00:31:44,249 --> 00:31:46,958
We have to pass
both Professor Do and Professor Ahn?

370
00:31:46,958 --> 00:31:50,441
The whole Han Eum knows
that Professor Do aims to dissolve the losers.

371
00:31:50,441 --> 00:31:53,410
If you're not confident, then practice.

372
00:31:55,926 --> 00:31:58,195
Then confidence will come.

373
00:31:59,583 --> 00:32:02,620
Some 'no name' is saying
something I can't understand.

374
00:32:04,219 --> 00:32:05,653
Sunbae...

375
00:32:06,724 --> 00:32:08,592
Il Lak!

376
00:32:27,659 --> 00:32:31,529
She should run over here,
calling me 'Yoo Jin' by now...

377
00:32:33,039 --> 00:32:35,379
Is she really not going
to follow me around anymore?

378
00:32:37,254 --> 00:32:39,389
She wouldn't give me time to think before.

379
00:32:40,217 --> 00:32:42,219
Why is she so busy these days?

380
00:32:48,428 --> 00:32:49,750
Good job, Nae Il.

381
00:32:49,750 --> 00:32:51,583
Mini Min Hee...

382
00:32:51,583 --> 00:32:55,939
- Let's have a snack.
- Really? I was hungry. I'm glad.

383
00:33:01,045 --> 00:33:03,781
Did you forget anything?

384
00:33:05,238 --> 00:33:07,240
You forgot the cream.

385
00:33:14,058 --> 00:33:15,693
It's sesame seeds, right?

386
00:33:16,831 --> 00:33:18,833
More please!

387
00:33:18,833 --> 00:33:20,864
Is our new sesame cake good?

388
00:33:24,268 --> 00:33:27,504
Mini Min Hee, I'll get going first.

389
00:33:29,135 --> 00:33:30,249
Nae Il...

390
00:33:30,249 --> 00:33:32,309
Sorry.

391
00:33:32,309 --> 00:33:36,541
What's wrong with Nae Il today?
She's acting strange.

392
00:33:36,541 --> 00:33:38,249
You said she's been sick
since the classical night.

393
00:33:38,249 --> 00:33:40,315
Is she okay now?

394
00:33:40,315 --> 00:33:44,819
I don't know.
We're all sick because of Yoo Jin.

395
00:33:44,819 --> 00:33:46,420
With Yoo Jin, why?

396
00:33:47,644 --> 00:33:52,042
I got caught completely.

397
00:33:52,042 --> 00:33:54,231
I even took a picture with him...

398
00:33:54,231 --> 00:33:57,901
Yes. I'm totally disappointed, boss.

399
00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:05,309
Why are the kids all like that?

400
00:34:09,475 --> 00:34:11,549
Stop being overly involved in school.

401
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:13,384
You always run after your son's matters.

402
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:14,708
How can I not?

403
00:34:14,708 --> 00:34:17,249
Why did you put my son
through this odd business?

404
00:34:17,249 --> 00:34:21,624
I'm sorry. But I only discussed with him.

405
00:34:21,624 --> 00:34:24,595
It was your son, Yoo Jin, who suggested...

406
00:34:25,522 --> 00:34:30,833
But both of us will be blamed anyway.

407
00:34:30,833 --> 00:34:33,449
So why did you pull Yoo Jin into it?

408
00:34:33,449 --> 00:34:35,283
My Yoo Jin...

409
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:38,083
If you ever hurt him...

410
00:34:38,083 --> 00:34:41,311
Did I ever do that?
You and Cha Dong Woo...

411
00:34:42,553 --> 00:34:44,721
Sorry...

412
00:34:45,714 --> 00:34:47,663
Forget it.

413
00:34:47,663 --> 00:34:51,415
That man always have been hurting Yoo Jin.

414
00:34:51,415 --> 00:34:54,464
Dong Woo doesn't show himself at all.

415
00:34:54,464 --> 00:34:57,644
The chairwoman of the board sends an invitation
to him for every concert.

416
00:34:58,307 --> 00:35:00,708
Would he be the kind
to come to school concerts?

417
00:35:00,708 --> 00:35:04,802
He even ignores his son
if he's not the best.

418
00:35:06,109 --> 00:35:08,311
I hope I never get to see him again.

419
00:35:12,666 --> 00:35:14,500
[Franz]

420
00:35:17,414 --> 00:35:19,750
You think you can make it up
to me that easily?

421
00:35:37,807 --> 00:35:39,475
Why the heck are you here?

422
00:35:40,424 --> 00:35:42,539
I'm moving in.

423
00:35:42,539 --> 00:35:43,750
Second floor of this building.

424
00:35:43,750 --> 00:35:47,146
Second floor? Why here?

425
00:35:47,146 --> 00:35:48,833
What do you mean, why?

426
00:35:48,833 --> 00:35:52,042
Because I needed a place to live.

427
00:35:52,042 --> 00:35:54,418
We'll see each other often now.

428
00:35:54,418 --> 00:35:55,986
Let's get along.

429
00:36:16,273 --> 00:36:18,916
He's everywhere I go.

430
00:36:18,916 --> 00:36:21,545
At Yoo Il Lak's restaurant,
at S Orchestra...

431
00:36:21,545 --> 00:36:23,541
with Seol Nae Il, eating with Seol Nae Il

432
00:36:23,541 --> 00:36:25,849
or earning points from Seol Nae Il.

433
00:36:27,418 --> 00:36:29,553
What is he up to?

434
00:36:35,018 --> 00:36:38,555
That's nonsense.
How is that possible with Seol Nae Il...

435
00:36:53,339 --> 00:36:55,291
I'm inviting you to my house-warming party.

436
00:36:55,291 --> 00:36:58,982
I'm attaching my address with a map below.

437
00:37:05,309 --> 00:37:07,833
I should've bought you toilet paper
for your party.

438
00:37:07,833 --> 00:37:10,627
- Drink up!
- Drink up!

439
00:37:12,363 --> 00:37:13,864
You came!

440
00:37:16,166 --> 00:37:19,370
By the way, a floor below my place
is your place?

441
00:37:19,370 --> 00:37:20,916
Isn't it strange?

442
00:37:20,916 --> 00:37:23,249
The place I was looking for
just became available.

443
00:37:23,249 --> 00:37:26,539
Suspicious. Suspicious.

444
00:37:26,539 --> 00:37:28,708
Hurry up and sit down!
The meat is getting burnt!

445
00:37:28,708 --> 00:37:30,166
This is a great place.

446
00:37:30,166 --> 00:37:32,716
Yoo Jin makes a big fuss
that the smell will linger in his place.

447
00:37:32,716 --> 00:37:34,484
But Yoon Hoo...

448
00:37:35,089 --> 00:37:37,833
I wonder if Almighty Cha had dinner.

449
00:37:37,833 --> 00:37:41,416
I told you to just ignore him. Just eat!

450
00:37:41,416 --> 00:37:44,295
- Yoon Hoo, You should eat too.
- Okay. Enjoy, everyone.

451
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:45,750
Hey hey hey!

452
00:37:45,750 --> 00:37:47,791
What kind of a girl eats like that?

453
00:37:47,791 --> 00:37:49,207
And why didn't you get any taller
eating like that?

454
00:37:49,207 --> 00:37:51,702
I have an older brother
who takes away food from me just like Lak.

455
00:37:51,702 --> 00:37:52,833
He ate all to himself
and grew all to himself.

456
00:37:52,833 --> 00:37:54,438
When did I ever take yours?

457
00:37:54,438 --> 00:37:57,041
- Give that to me!
- No, it's mine!

458
00:37:57,041 --> 00:37:59,409
Mini Min Hee, eat fast!

459
00:38:20,551 --> 00:38:23,583
- I ate too much.
- Let's have another party soon.

460
00:38:23,583 --> 00:38:27,374
- You don't need to see us off.
- Go inside.

461
00:38:27,374 --> 00:38:30,407
- See you tomorrow!
- Bye.

462
00:38:36,380 --> 00:38:39,291
Doesn't Nae Il look like a woman?

463
00:38:39,291 --> 00:38:41,155
Was Nae Il ever a man?

464
00:38:41,155 --> 00:38:42,750
A woman becomes a lady

465
00:38:42,750 --> 00:38:46,207
in front of a guy
who treats her like a princess.

466
00:38:46,207 --> 00:38:47,424
- Is that right?
- Is that right?

467
00:38:47,424 --> 00:38:49,960
- Let's go home.
- I'm so full.

468
00:38:50,860 --> 00:38:54,564
Yoon Hoo, I'll go home now.

469
00:38:55,473 --> 00:38:57,291
Nae Il.

470
00:38:57,291 --> 00:38:58,535
Yes?

471
00:38:59,509 --> 00:39:02,812
Will you play a duet with me?

472
00:39:03,459 --> 00:39:05,175
Why me?

473
00:39:05,175 --> 00:39:07,978
I want to perform with your piano.

474
00:39:08,893 --> 00:39:11,295
I'd like you to consider it seriously.

475
00:39:13,497 --> 00:39:18,401
Is it really important
to play a duet with me?

476
00:39:20,690 --> 00:39:24,393
- It's not important.
- Right?

477
00:39:26,663 --> 00:39:28,732
I thought maybe...

478
00:39:29,892 --> 00:39:34,630
Yoon Hoo, thank you for today.
I'll get back in now.

479
00:39:37,013 --> 00:39:38,514
I'm desperate.

480
00:39:44,031 --> 00:39:49,958
Since I heard you play 'Water Game'
at Yoon Yi Song Music Festival,

481
00:39:49,958 --> 00:39:52,789
I've thought about that the whole time.

482
00:39:55,325 --> 00:39:59,695
I want to play with you.

483
00:40:01,304 --> 00:40:04,974
More than how much you want
to play with Cha Yoo Jin.

484
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:15,543
I want to play Grieg's piano concerto
just like you.

485
00:40:15,543 --> 00:40:20,080
Intense, vivid and splendid.

486
00:40:22,979 --> 00:40:26,415
I've never played like that.

487
00:40:37,583 --> 00:40:39,334
[International call]

488
00:40:41,083 --> 00:40:42,526
Hello?

489
00:40:42,526 --> 00:40:43,916
Why does it take so long

490
00:40:43,916 --> 00:40:45,976
to answer the phone, my apprentice?

491
00:40:47,061 --> 00:40:48,333
Professor?

492
00:40:48,333 --> 00:40:52,207
Mi Na doesn't answer my calls.

493
00:40:52,207 --> 00:40:55,185
I'm allowed one call every three days.

494
00:40:55,185 --> 00:40:58,755
I'm wasting that call on you...

495
00:40:59,745 --> 00:41:01,708
I'm glad to hear that you're doing well.

496
00:41:01,708 --> 00:41:04,840
Have you gone deaf?

497
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:06,697
I'm not doing very well.

498
00:41:06,697 --> 00:41:09,366
Mi Na doesn't answer my calls.

499
00:41:09,366 --> 00:41:12,333
Would she want to answer the phone
after you left like that?

500
00:41:12,333 --> 00:41:16,439
I didn't run away this time.

501
00:41:30,667 --> 00:41:32,768
I was dragged here.

502
00:41:33,710 --> 00:41:36,693
So why did you run away before the concert?

503
00:41:36,693 --> 00:41:38,833
This is why I ran away.

504
00:41:38,833 --> 00:41:42,266
Practice, practice for 24 hours...

505
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:44,568
They suffocated me.

506
00:41:46,803 --> 00:41:51,174
I understand. I'll talk to Ms. Dean.

507
00:41:51,174 --> 00:41:52,791
I'll ask her to answer the phone.

508
00:41:52,791 --> 00:41:54,644
Of course you should.

509
00:41:58,855 --> 00:42:02,725
What's with the big sigh for a young man?

510
00:42:05,693 --> 00:42:09,624
Do you feel frustrated
because Baby is too slow?

511
00:42:09,624 --> 00:42:14,030
You want to fly, but Baby can't even walk?

512
00:42:15,109 --> 00:42:20,458
By the way, my apprentice,
why do you want to make Baby fly?

513
00:42:20,458 --> 00:42:22,958
It's a waste of talent
to leave her like that.

514
00:42:22,958 --> 00:42:25,142
Why does she get ignored with that talent?

515
00:42:25,142 --> 00:42:28,545
- Brag about it and show off...
- Why would you?

516
00:42:28,545 --> 00:42:30,780
Why do you want to brag about it?

517
00:43:15,763 --> 00:43:17,583
Up to here.

518
00:43:17,583 --> 00:43:20,530
What do you think?
It's the our duet performance.

519
00:43:28,438 --> 00:43:29,973
Our duet?

520
00:43:30,653 --> 00:43:32,875
Don't you think it'll be really fun?

521
00:43:32,875 --> 00:43:35,958
I'm going to try it with you.

522
00:43:35,958 --> 00:43:37,814
I want to try it.

523
00:43:42,738 --> 00:43:44,707
Thank you.

524
00:43:57,888 --> 00:44:00,166
Don't be too late...

525
00:44:00,166 --> 00:44:05,642
with expressing and admitting your feelings.

526
00:44:07,751 --> 00:44:09,834
[Han Eum Orchestra Audition]

527
00:44:13,683 --> 00:44:16,085
It looks like you're avoiding me these days.

528
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:19,556
I'm not avoiding you, but it's a bit...

529
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:22,583
I know it's a bit weird,
but we still have to meet.

530
00:44:22,583 --> 00:44:24,042
Do I have to come and find you?

531
00:44:24,042 --> 00:44:27,597
If you come find me, I can't refuse you...

532
00:44:29,294 --> 00:44:31,249
I still can't!

533
00:44:31,249 --> 00:44:34,875
Our relationship is like Romeo and Juliet,
like North and South now!

534
00:44:34,875 --> 00:44:38,833
What are you saying?
We discuss this as bandmasters.

535
00:44:38,833 --> 00:44:40,783
Bandmasters?

536
00:44:41,545 --> 00:44:46,683
You... me... we're bandmasters. That's right.

537
00:44:59,429 --> 00:45:01,875
You must be hungry. Let's eat and talk.

538
00:45:01,875 --> 00:45:04,624
Why did you bring so much?
I can't eat this much.

539
00:45:04,624 --> 00:45:09,222
It's not just for you. I'm hungry, too.
We can eat it together.

540
00:45:21,641 --> 00:45:23,569
What?

541
00:45:23,569 --> 00:45:25,000
Do I have something on my lips?

542
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:27,931
No! You don't have anything on your lips.

543
00:45:31,274 --> 00:45:33,776
Are you going to get played by Cha Yoo Jin?

544
00:45:35,781 --> 00:45:38,335
Then what else? What are you going to do?

545
00:45:38,335 --> 00:45:42,083
You don't want
the blind audition either, do you?

546
00:45:42,083 --> 00:45:45,958
Same for me.
I can never let that happen to my members.

547
00:45:45,958 --> 00:45:49,412
Their pride is everything for them.
About half of them will leave.

548
00:45:49,412 --> 00:45:50,458
What about us?

549
00:45:50,458 --> 00:45:52,878
You think we'll go for the audition
because we have no pride?

550
00:45:52,878 --> 00:45:54,333
Let them leave if they can't do it.

551
00:45:54,333 --> 00:45:56,416
We don't need to fight between us.

552
00:45:56,416 --> 00:45:59,589
- We have a public enemy.
- Public enemy?

553
00:46:03,026 --> 00:46:04,394
Yoo Jin?

554
00:46:05,603 --> 00:46:07,374
Will you be really okay?

555
00:46:07,374 --> 00:46:10,033
The students seem to have
a deep misunderstanding.

556
00:46:10,933 --> 00:46:13,499
They'll realize it after the audition.

557
00:46:13,499 --> 00:46:16,624
If anything goes wrong...

558
00:46:16,624 --> 00:46:18,408
That won't happen.

559
00:46:19,032 --> 00:46:20,567
Madam Dean...

560
00:46:23,012 --> 00:46:28,217
Once the audition is over,
I plan to go back to where I was, too.

561
00:46:31,261 --> 00:46:34,430
Yes, I'm going to do that.

562
00:46:37,254 --> 00:46:40,890
Let's boycott Cha Yoo Jin's blind audition.

563
00:46:41,872 --> 00:46:43,366
Boycott?

564
00:46:43,366 --> 00:46:47,541
If no one goes from A and S,
we can cancel this audition.

565
00:46:47,541 --> 00:46:50,740
And I don't want to get played
by the dean or Cha Yoo Jin anymore.

566
00:46:53,450 --> 00:46:58,188
What do you think?
If we unite, we can cancel this audition.

567
00:47:01,484 --> 00:47:03,152
Boycott?

568
00:47:03,152 --> 00:47:07,035
Yes, we decided
to boycott the blind audition.

569
00:47:07,035 --> 00:47:09,833
Is it okay for us to do this to Almighty Cha?

570
00:47:09,833 --> 00:47:11,794
You still haven't come to your senses!

571
00:47:12,815 --> 00:47:14,958
Don't tell Nae Il and Yoon Hoo.

572
00:47:14,958 --> 00:47:17,045
They won't go to the audition anyway.

573
00:47:17,045 --> 00:47:19,501
Is A Orchestra really not going to do it?

574
00:47:20,549 --> 00:47:23,042
Can we really do this?

575
00:47:23,042 --> 00:47:25,875
Cha Yoo Jin needs to experience failure, too.

576
00:47:25,875 --> 00:47:27,499
He's never experienced it

577
00:47:27,499 --> 00:47:29,900
when everyone else went through it
all the time.

578
00:47:33,149 --> 00:47:36,333
No one signed up for the audition?

579
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:38,750
No members from S and A?

580
00:47:38,750 --> 00:47:40,416
I don't know what they're thinking,

581
00:47:40,416 --> 00:47:42,659
but it seems
that they're boycotting it as a group.

582
00:47:44,060 --> 00:47:46,729
Does Yoo Jin know about it by any chance?

583
00:47:48,621 --> 00:47:51,924
Cha Yoo Jin, the class is starting soon!
Where are you going?

584
00:47:58,712 --> 00:48:00,310
Jung Shi Won.

585
00:48:00,310 --> 00:48:02,499
What are you doing? This is not like you.

586
00:48:02,499 --> 00:48:04,916
It's not a disadvantageous audition
to you guys.

587
00:48:04,916 --> 00:48:06,708
It's based on skills,
so why are you avoiding it?

588
00:48:06,708 --> 00:48:12,059
A Orchestra may have been a group
that's possessed with an elite mindset.

589
00:48:12,059 --> 00:48:14,207
But it was precious to me as a bandmaster.

590
00:48:14,207 --> 00:48:16,726
But you and the dean destroyed it.

591
00:48:17,817 --> 00:48:20,668
Do other members of A think that way too?

592
00:48:22,739 --> 00:48:24,759
Half of you will leave to study abroad soon.

593
00:48:25,489 --> 00:48:27,708
An orchestra to them?

594
00:48:27,708 --> 00:48:30,573
It's only a resume builder and an experience.

595
00:48:56,481 --> 00:48:58,216
Here is the application.

596
00:49:03,007 --> 00:49:05,008
You came all the way here to give me this?

597
00:49:05,008 --> 00:49:06,583
Great.

598
00:49:06,583 --> 00:49:08,750
This is not like you.

599
00:49:08,750 --> 00:49:10,867
It's a good opportunity
and it's the last opportunity.

600
00:49:10,867 --> 00:49:12,833
Don't try to lecture me.

601
00:49:12,833 --> 00:49:15,866
I listened to you as a conductor,
but not anymore.

602
00:49:15,866 --> 00:49:18,291
- Why can't you believe it?
- You abandoned us and left us.

603
00:49:18,291 --> 00:49:20,357
Not me, yourselves!

604
00:49:20,357 --> 00:49:22,959
- What?
- I believe that you'll get in...

605
00:49:23,667 --> 00:49:25,921
but why can't you believe in yourself?

606
00:49:25,921 --> 00:49:28,131
Like you said, I'm your conductor.

607
00:49:28,131 --> 00:49:31,601
I know all of you more than anyone else.
And I'm saying that you'll get in!

608
00:50:18,268 --> 00:50:20,958
Is it about a guy or a girl?

609
00:50:20,958 --> 00:50:22,624
If it's about a girl,

610
00:50:22,624 --> 00:50:25,361
I wouldn't have a headache
or feel so unjustified.

611
00:50:26,589 --> 00:50:28,750
Father.

612
00:50:28,750 --> 00:50:30,708
I'm really not sure.

613
00:50:30,708 --> 00:50:32,595
Why did Yoo Jin do that?

614
00:50:34,257 --> 00:50:36,659
Did he really try to shake us off?

615
00:50:38,301 --> 00:50:40,875
But more than that,

616
00:50:40,875 --> 00:50:45,675
I just hate him and want to punch him.

617
00:50:50,220 --> 00:50:54,757
My Il Lak must have liked Yoo Jin a lot.

618
00:50:56,309 --> 00:50:59,913
When your feelings are deep,
the rough will deepen, too.

619
00:51:23,962 --> 00:51:26,000
What's wrong?

620
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:27,624
What do you mean?

621
00:51:27,624 --> 00:51:29,285
Why don't you follow me around?

622
00:51:30,426 --> 00:51:35,431
Even if I felt tired,
you used to follow me around like a puppy.

623
00:51:36,512 --> 00:51:39,648
- You were tired of me.
- But you still followed me around.

624
00:51:41,046 --> 00:51:45,602
You dragged me into your dumpster house
and followed me around all you want.

625
00:51:45,602 --> 00:51:47,170
You came into my place without permission...

626
00:51:47,170 --> 00:51:48,871
And you didn't like that.

627
00:51:51,674 --> 00:51:53,054
Of course I didn't like it.

628
00:51:55,711 --> 00:51:59,748
You don't like it,
so I'm not going to do it anymore.

629
00:52:20,570 --> 00:52:23,063
Sunbae...

630
00:52:23,063 --> 00:52:25,896
Sunbae!

631
00:52:25,896 --> 00:52:28,833
Sunbae, you can't sleep here.

632
00:52:28,833 --> 00:52:30,880
You'll catch a cold.

633
00:52:45,961 --> 00:52:48,530
She does whatever she wants.

634
00:53:09,152 --> 00:53:11,903
Did he drink?

635
00:53:11,903 --> 00:53:14,035
He smelled like alcohol.

636
00:53:49,854 --> 00:53:52,124
Professor Ahn is coming soon.

637
00:53:52,124 --> 00:53:54,497
I heard no one applied for the audition.

638
00:53:56,199 --> 00:54:00,469
Then of course the audition will be canceled.

639
00:54:25,769 --> 00:54:29,473
No one actually showed up?

640
00:54:52,588 --> 00:54:55,324
Sunbae looks really nervous.

641
00:54:56,986 --> 00:54:58,554
What's going on?

642
00:54:59,295 --> 00:55:01,249
Hi, Mini Min Hee.

643
00:55:01,249 --> 00:55:04,734
What's going on?
How come no one's coming to the audition?

644
00:55:07,970 --> 00:55:11,607
What? You're boycotting?

645
00:55:14,689 --> 00:55:16,833
All of A and S?

646
00:55:16,833 --> 00:55:21,017
If we told you, you'd have told Yoo Jin.

647
00:55:21,017 --> 00:55:23,166
So we didn't tell you.

648
00:55:23,166 --> 00:55:25,554
Hey, that's too mean.

649
00:55:27,190 --> 00:55:30,458
Then what happens to Sunbae?

650
00:55:30,458 --> 00:55:31,750
I don't know.

651
00:55:31,750 --> 00:55:34,708
I'm sure
he'll take responsibility with the dean.

652
00:55:34,708 --> 00:55:37,000
I'm hanging up
if you don't have any more to say.

653
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,602
Hello? Mini Min Hee!

654
00:55:51,851 --> 00:55:54,416
What's going on? You could have just called.

655
00:55:54,416 --> 00:55:59,322
Lak, I heard
you're boycotting Yoo Jin's audition.

656
00:55:59,322 --> 00:56:01,583
Don't blame Lak.

657
00:56:01,583 --> 00:56:04,093
All of us decided on it together.

658
00:56:04,093 --> 00:56:06,028
Why would we become the sidekick of A?

659
00:56:06,028 --> 00:56:09,532
No, it could be the last chance given to us.

660
00:56:09,532 --> 00:56:11,207
If he was going to give us a chance,

661
00:56:11,207 --> 00:56:13,674
he wouldn't have left us
knowing that we'd dissolve.

662
00:56:21,144 --> 00:56:25,514
But it was Yoo Jin Sunbae.

663
00:56:26,511 --> 00:56:27,333
What do you mean?

664
00:56:27,333 --> 00:56:32,000
When Milch abandoned us,
the first person who ran over to see us.

665
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:34,750
And when we had the Mambo performance

666
00:56:34,750 --> 00:56:38,434
he came right over after getting the text
about our conductor's disappearance.

667
00:56:39,152 --> 00:56:40,587
Really?

668
00:57:24,197 --> 00:57:28,301
No one is coming to audition?

669
00:57:31,714 --> 00:57:33,482
No.

670
00:57:35,318 --> 00:57:37,520
What the heck.

671
00:57:38,268 --> 00:57:43,206
I thought they'd believe me
after all the time we spent together.

672
00:57:46,528 --> 00:57:49,398
How do they know when you don't say anything?

673
00:57:49,398 --> 00:57:52,701
You think by yourself,
you decide by yourself...

674
00:57:54,770 --> 00:57:57,342
You've never asked us about our thoughts.

675
00:58:07,741 --> 00:58:09,909
About Professor Do...

676
00:58:10,979 --> 00:58:14,348
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

677
00:58:15,995 --> 00:58:19,207
I knew you'd be scared,
but I still sent you there.

678
00:58:19,207 --> 00:58:21,964
I shouldn't have done that.

679
00:58:21,964 --> 00:58:24,533
I should've asked you first.

680
00:58:25,514 --> 00:58:27,549
I only thought about myself.

681
00:58:29,230 --> 00:58:31,032
Because I was doing it for you.

682
00:58:32,048 --> 00:58:34,016
I thought it would be okay.

683
00:58:42,971 --> 00:58:44,573
I am sorry.

684
00:58:51,951 --> 00:58:55,821
I am actually thankful...

685
00:58:59,001 --> 00:59:01,737
that you tried to give us a chance.

686
00:59:23,259 --> 00:59:25,327
How come no one's coming?

687
00:59:28,985 --> 00:59:31,000
Why don't we wait a little longer?

688
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:33,333
If they were going to come,
they would've came long ago.

689
00:59:33,333 --> 00:59:35,871
How can judges wait for students?

690
00:59:37,243 --> 00:59:38,416
Just a little longer...

691
00:59:38,416 --> 00:59:41,750
Professor, should we start now?
It's almost time.

692
00:59:41,750 --> 00:59:45,915
- Start what?
- The audition. Everyone's on standby.

693
00:59:49,685 --> 00:59:51,925
Should we believe in Cha Yoo Jin?

694
00:59:51,925 --> 00:59:53,875
He said he believed in us.

695
00:59:53,875 --> 00:59:57,458
When I think about who believed in us,
he was the only one.

696
00:59:57,458 --> 01:00:00,329
Sorry, I'm going first.

697
01:00:06,702 --> 01:00:10,042
Did you see the text? Lak is a traitor...

698
01:00:10,042 --> 01:00:12,675
He told us to boycott the audition,
but he went there by himself now.

699
01:00:12,675 --> 01:00:14,333
I know.

700
01:00:14,333 --> 01:00:16,791
By the way,
where are you going, Mini Min Hee?

701
01:00:16,791 --> 01:00:19,715
What? Me?

702
01:00:21,183 --> 01:00:22,875
What about you, Su Min?

703
01:00:22,875 --> 01:00:25,388
Me? I'm just...

704
01:00:25,388 --> 01:00:27,458
Let's just go! Hurry!

705
01:00:27,458 --> 01:00:29,207
Let's go!

706
01:00:29,207 --> 01:00:33,562
Student from A wouldn't come first,
so it must be a student from S.

707
01:00:33,562 --> 01:00:37,624
But I'm still relieved.
I guess they decided not to boycott anymore.

708
01:00:37,624 --> 01:00:38,947
Even so...

709
01:00:39,669 --> 01:00:42,374
they wouldn't get in with their level anyway.

710
01:00:42,374 --> 01:00:44,381
Why bother coming here?

711
01:02:07,685 --> 01:02:09,333
The boycott is off.

712
01:02:09,333 --> 01:02:11,293
Yoo Il Lak went to the audition.

713
01:02:11,293 --> 01:02:14,029
There is no reason to go
unless it's the top performance.

714
01:02:14,029 --> 01:02:15,750
Make that happen.

715
01:02:15,750 --> 01:02:19,027
I should have believed in you guys
and gone together.

716
01:02:19,027 --> 01:02:23,045
Let's just get through today.
No, just half a day.

717
01:02:23,045 --> 01:02:26,130
The only thing left is dating.

718
01:02:26,130 --> 01:02:27,443
Let me know when the fight is over.

719
01:02:27,443 --> 01:02:29,540
That's when we'll begin our practice.

720
01:02:29,540 --> 01:02:32,666
Son Soo Ji?
The world-famous pianist from Korea!

721
01:02:32,666 --> 01:02:36,852
That's my seat, for Yoo Jin Sunbae and me.
